Toslink extension: source re-assert while the signal persists.

Problem: toslink activation is EDGE-based (only on a signal transition
no-signal -> signal). If a Spotify playback runs in parallel and is paused,
Beocreate's determineCurrentSource sets currentSource=null (it does not fall
back to the lower-priority but still active Optical source). Since the optical
signal is present continuously, there is no signal edge — Optical is never
re-activated and Now-Playing stays empty, even though the TOSLINK audio is
immediately audible again.

Fix: during polling, additionally re-activate when a signal is present AND no
source is active (sources.getCurrentSource() == null). Does NOT steal focus
from Spotify while Spotify is active (then getCurrentSource() != null).

Note: the full patched file is versioned at
deploy/beo-extensions/toslink/index.js (upstream + null check + this re-assert).

--- a/beo-extensions/toslink/index.js
+++ b/beo-extensions/toslink/index.js
@@ -247,6 +247,12 @@
 									if (sources) sources.sourceActivated("toslink", "playing");
 								}
 								//if (debug) console.log("Toslink activated.");
-							}
+							} else if (settings.toslinkEnabled && sources && sources.getCurrentSource && !sources.getCurrentSource()) {
+								// Signal still present but no source active (e.g. Spotify paused):
+								// re-assert Optical as the active source.
+								toslinkActive = true;
+								if (sources) sources.sourceActivated("toslink", "playing");
+							}
 						} else if (response.dec == 0) {
